From 90140ee9afd267c068b71e539027e3cffa33fcb2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nagarajan Maran <nmaran@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 4 Sep 2025 12:32:43 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] QSDK:CP:wifi:mac80211: Add WAR to handle non-assoc
 link's assoc failure

Prevent firmware crash caused by non-associated link's association
failure in WDS STA side.

In previous design, ath12k_mac_op_unassign_vif_chanctx handled
vdev stop and delete. With the latest package upgrade, this is now
split: ath12k_mac_op_change_sta_links handles stop, and
ath12k_mac_op_change_vif_links handles delete.

When assoc fails for a non-associated link,
ath12k_mac_op_change_sta_links is not invoked, causing vdev to be
deleted without a stop, leading to firmware crash. A workaround was
introduced to activate the failed link and later triggering
ath12k_mac_op_change_sta_links, ensuring proper vdev deletion.
However this link activation, changes the primary link id of the
STA to non-assoc link.

Fix regression where ahsta->primary_link_id is incorrectly set to
non-associated link in two-link WDS STA MLD setup. Prevent crash by
updating primary_link_id in STA vdev, only when selected link has
successful association status. This change is also a workaround and
a full redesign of assoc failure handling in mac80211 and ath12k is
recommended.

Fixes: 823b06947b14 ("UPSTREAM:CP: wifi: mac80211: Handle non-assoc link connection failure")
Patch-dependency:
    306-UPSTREAM-CP-wifi-mac80211-Handle-non-assoc-link-conn.patch

Signed-off-by: Nagarajan Maran <nmaran@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 include/net/mac80211.h |  1 +
 net/mac80211/util.c    | 20 ++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 21 insertions(+)

diff --git a/include/net/mac80211.h b/include/net/mac80211.h
index 9bb1edc5fd3a..c6c0fb2be536 100644
--- a/include/net/mac80211.h
+++ b/include/net/mac80211.h
@@ -8489,4 +8489,5 @@ ieee80211_rx_send_mscs_tuple(struct ieee80211_sta *pubsta,
  */
 int ieee80211_get_radio_idx_by_freq(struct wiphy *wiphy, u32 freq);
 
+int ieee80211_get_link_assoc_status(struct ieee80211_vif *vif, u8 link_id);
 #endif /* MAC80211_H */
diff --git a/net/mac80211/util.c b/net/mac80211/util.c
index da1a857be32c..fae279666811 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/util.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/util.c
@@ -5241,3 +5241,23 @@ int ieee80211_get_radio_idx_by_freq(struct wiphy *wiphy, u32 freq)
 	return -1;
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(ieee80211_get_radio_idx_by_freq);
+
+int ieee80211_get_link_assoc_status(struct ieee80211_vif *vif, u8 link_id)
+{
+	struct ieee80211_sub_if_data *sdata = NULL;
+	struct ieee80211_mgd_assoc_data *assoc_data = NULL;
+
+	if (link_id >= IEEE80211_MLD_MAX_NUM_LINKS)
+		return -1;
+
+	sdata = vif_to_sdata(vif);
+	if (!sdata)
+		return -1;
+
+	assoc_data = sdata->u.mgd.assoc_data;
+	if (!assoc_data)
+		return -1;
+
+	return (int)assoc_data->link[link_id].status;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL(ieee80211_get_link_assoc_status);
